-- Atria Centralizes Russian Meat Production in St. Petersburg, Cuts 300 Jobs
-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 2010-11-26T06:03:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/atria-centralizes-russian-meat-production-in-st-petersburg-cuts-300-jobs.html
Atria Oyj will centralize its
Russian meat production operations in St. Petersburg from Moscow
and Sinyavino and plans to cut 300 jobs.  Atria expects annual cost savings of 6 million euros from
the cuts and will book a one-time cost of 1.5 million euros,
mostly in 2011, the company said in a statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kati Pohjanpalo at 
 kpohjanpalo@bloomberg.net  